<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1">
  <title>HTML Hyperlinks: Text, Image, Audio, Video</title>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1>WebPage Assignment</h1>
    <p>
      Shows two semantic elements (header, article) and two non-semantic elements (div, span).
    </p>
  </header>

  <!-- Semantic element 2: article -->
  <article>
    <h2>1. Text hyperlink</h2>
    <p>
      Simple text link. Opens in a new tab.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="https://example.com" target="_blank">Visit example.com (text link)</a>
    </p>

    <h2>2. Image hyperlink</h2>
    <p>
      Click the image to open the full-size file.
    </p>
    <div class="row">
      <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/html/pic_trulli.jpg">
        <img src="https://www.w3schools.com/html/pic_trulli.jpg" alt="Trulli" />
    </a>
    <div>
      <p>
        Or use a text link for the same image:
      </p>
      <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/html/pic_trulli.jpg">Open full image</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>3. Audio hyperlink</h2>
  <p>
    Link that points to an audio file and a player to preview it.
  </p>
  <p>
    <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/html/horse.mp3" target="_blank">Open audio file (MP3)</a>
  </p>
  <audio controls src="https://www.w3schools.com/html/horse.mp3">Your browser does not support the audio element.</audio>

  <h2>4. Video hyperlink</h2>
  <p>
    Link to a video file and an embedded player.
  </p>
  <p>
    <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/html/mov_bbb.mp4" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open MP4 in new tab</a>
  </p>
  <video controls width="320" src="https://www.w3schools.com/html/mov_bbb.mp4">Your browser does not support the video element.</video>

  <h2>5. Using a span (non-semantic inline element)</h2>
  <p>
    Inline styling and a small inline link. <span>Note:</span> the span itself is not a link. It contains one.
  </p>
  <p>
    <span>Find more: </span><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML">MDN HTML docs</a>
  </p>

  <h2>6. Using a div (non-semantic block element)</h2>
  <div>
    This is a div element content
  </div>
</article>

<footer>
  <p>
    This is a footer element 
  </p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
